I tightened the shared sync layer in [sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts) and added regressions in [sync-node.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.test.ts). The concrete fixes are:
- encrypted session metadata no longer wipes `SessionInfo`; `SyncNode` now preserves session identity fields while decoding opaque metadata
- todos are now actually derived from `TodoWrite` tool parts in the message stream
- the server auth boundary in [syncNodeToken.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/auth/syncNodeToken.ts) now validates claims through the shared `happy-sync` schema artifact without breaking the standalone server runtime

